cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper discusses the use of tethered unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) to enhance the coverage and capacity of cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the design and control of the UAVs, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). The proposed system involves data and energy transfer between the UAV and the ground station, which can be considered as a control system, leading to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the security and privacy concerns of the proposed system, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed system, including video surveillance and disaster response, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
